title: Unsycing the contacts from another GMAIL account
content:
I accidentally enabled sync from another GMAIL account, other than then main account.
So now I have most of them duplicate and some of them are obselete.

So now I want to cleanup the Synced data. I tried these:

Disabled Sync for second account.
Cleared Cache / storage for Contacts and Phone.

Still I see the contacts are there. â€Œ When open such contact, I see that it shows both Duo & WhatsApp also in that, though not editable.

How can I unsync? I see many suggestions from internet, but not working in the current Pixel (Android 9)
